			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>iCoLa: A Compositional Meta-language with Support for Incremental Language Development</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/DamianFrölich.html">Damian Frölich</a>, <a href="../profile/LThomasvanBinsbergen.html">L. Thomas van Binsbergen</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567529">10.1145/3567512.3567529</a></li>
<li>Original shorter version of <a href="../sle2024s/paper04.html"><em>iCoLa+: An extensible meta-language with support for exploratory language development</em></a> (SLE 2024 SI)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagM">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> It proposes a compositional meta-language for defining languages incrementally.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The approach emphasizes modular composition of language components.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagL">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> Incremental development promotes reuse of existing language parts across iterations.
</li></ul></li></ul>
